main event: A low-flying object was observed orbiting in the northeast sky at very high speed over Lebanon, Ohio on April 7, 1960.
interesting points: The object was described as moving faster than anything the witness had ever seen, like a small rocket.
The object started close overhead and then headed northeast at very high, supersonic speeds.
The report mentions a previous sighting of the same or a similar object in December 1959, but it was not observed at that time.
The report was passed along with a request for clarification on the conflicting information.
The report contains sketches or drawings of the unidentified objects, but no clear photographs.
sighted object: a low-flying, fast-moving object in the sky
